{
    "publish_date": "2012-06-15T01:37:17.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT10M38S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "Hi, I\u2019m John Green;", 
            "dur": "1.18", 
            "start": "0.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "this is\nCrash Course: World History", 
            "dur": "1.2", 
            "start": "1.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and today we\u2019re going to do\nsome compare and contrast,", 
            "dur": "2.18", 
            "start": "3.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because that\u2019s what passes for\nhip in world history circles.", 
            "dur": "2.28", 
            "start": "5.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Right, so you\u2019ve probably heard of", 
            "dur": "1.229", 
            "start": "7.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Christopher Columbus who in 1492\nsailed the ocean blue", 
            "dur": "2.99", 
            "start": "8.809"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and discovered America, a place that\nhad been previously discovered", 
            "dur": "3.111", 
            "start": "11.799"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "only by millions of people--", 
            "dur": "1.28", 
            "start": "14.91"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Mr Green, Mr Green!", 
            "dur": "1.21", 
            "start": "16.19"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Columbus was just a lucky idiot.", 
            "dur": "1.549", 
            "start": "17.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Yeah, no.", 
            "dur": "0.701", 
            "start": "18.949"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Here\u2019s a little rule of thumb,\nMe from the Past:", 
            "dur": "1.879", 
            "start": "19.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you are not an expert in something,", 
            "dur": "1.681", 
            "start": "21.529"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "don\u2019t pretend to be an expert.", 
            "dur": "1.85", 
            "start": "23.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is going to serve you well\nboth in your academic career", 
            "dur": "2.93", 
            "start": "25.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and in your Kissing Career.", 
            "dur": "1.47", 
            "start": "27.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "MOVING ON.", 
            "dur": "1.12", 
            "start": "29.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[music intro]", 
            "dur": "1.47", 
            "start": "30.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[music intro]", 
            "dur": "1.48", 
            "start": "32.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[music intro]", 
            "dur": "1.47", 
            "start": "33.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[music intro]", 
            "dur": "1.47", 
            "start": "35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[music intro]", 
            "dur": "1.47", 
            "start": "36.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[music intro]", 
            "dur": "1.47", 
            "start": "37.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So unlike Me from the Past,", 
            "dur": "0.96", 
            "start": "39.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I\u2019d argue that Columbus has a\ndeserved reputation in history\u2014", 
            "dur": "2.5", 
            "start": "40.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[Save his Harry Potter\ndirectional stint]", 
            "dur": "0.25", 
            "start": "42.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but was he really the greatest sailor\nof the 15th Century?", 
            "dur": "2.63", 
            "start": "42.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, let\u2019s meet the other contestants.", 
            "dur": "1.33", 
            "start": "45.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[playing for a lifetime supply of Garlique]", 
            "dur": "0.78", 
            "start": "46.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In the red corner, we have Zheng He,\nwho, when it comes to ocean-going voyages", 
            "dur": "3.49", 
            "start": "47.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "was the first major figure of the 15th century.", 
            "dur": "3.16", 
            "start": "51.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And in the blue corner\nis Vasco da Gama,", 
            "dur": "2.31", 
            "start": "54.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "from scrappy little Portugal,\nwho managed to introduce Europeans", 
            "dur": "3.25", 
            "start": "56.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to the Indian Ocean trade network.", 
            "dur": "1.6", 
            "start": "59.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Columbus, you have to sit\nin the polka-dotted corner.", 
            "dur": "2.17", 
            "start": "61.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[until you learn special effects\nare a privilege, not a crutch]", 
            "dur": "0.569", 
            "start": "63.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "As you\u2019ll no doubt remember from\nour discussion of Indian Ocean trade,", 
            "dur": "2.2", 
            "start": "64.269"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it was dominated by\nMuslim merchants,", 
            "dur": "1.9", 
            "start": "66.469"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "involved ports in Africa and\nthe Middle East and", 
            "dur": "2.381", 
            "start": "68.369"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "India and Indonesia,\nand China and", 
            "dur": "2.06", 
            "start": "70.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it made a lot of people super rich.", 
            "dur": "2.299", 
            "start": "72.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This last point explains why our three\ncontestants were so eager to set sail.", 
            "dur": "3.411", 
            "start": "75.109"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, that and the ceaseless desire of\nhuman beings to discover things", 
            "dur": "3.32", 
            "start": "78.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and contract scurvy.", 
            "dur": "1.18", 
            "start": "81.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let\u2019s begin with Zheng He,", 
            "dur": "1.099", 
            "start": "83.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "who is probably the greatest admiral\nyou\u2019ve never have heard of.", 
            "dur": "2.551", 
            "start": "84.119"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Couple of important things about Zheng He:", 
            "dur": "1.549", 
            "start": "86.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "First, he was a Muslim.", 
            "dur": "1.271", 
            "start": "88.219"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That may seem strange until you consider that\nby the late 14th century China had long experience", 
            "dur": "4.11", 
            "start": "89.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with Muslims,", 
            "dur": "0.689", 
            "start": "93.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "especially when they were ruled by,\nwait for it....", 
            "dur": "3.26", 
            "start": "94.289"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The Mongols.", 
            "dur": "0.52", 
            "start": "97.549"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[Hark! The commotive, cacophonic\ncaterwauling of clattering conquerors!]", 
            "dur": "2.41", 
            "start": "98.069"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Secondly, Zheng He was a eunuch.", 
            "dur": "1.481", 
            "start": "100.479"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(He was one of a kind?]", 
            "dur": "0.88", 
            "start": "101.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Fortunately, 15th century China had\nexcellent general anesthesia,", 
            "dur": "2.61", 
            "start": "102.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so I\u2019m sure it didn\u2019t hurt at all\nwhen they castrated him\u2014", 
            "dur": "2.779", 
            "start": "105.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "what\u2019s that,\nStan?", 
            "dur": "0.75", 
            "start": "108.229"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They didn\u2019t have any anesthesia?", 
            "dur": "1.511", 
            "start": "108.979"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Oh, boy.", 
            "dur": "0.75", 
            "start": "110.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Oh. STAN,", 
            "dur": "0.75", 
            "start": "111.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I\u2019M SEEING IT!", 
            "dur": "0.85", 
            "start": "111.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I can see, AH AH AHHHH.", 
            "dur": "1.479", 
            "start": "112.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Stan!", 
            "dur": "0.25", 
            "start": "114.319"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "SHOW ME SOMETHING\nCUTE RIGGHT NOW!", 
            "dur": "1.55", 
            "start": "114.569"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Oh, hi there kitty!", 
            "dur": "1.371", 
            "start": "116.119"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How\u2019d you get in that little teacup?", 
            "dur": "2.409", 
            "start": "117.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Thank you,\nStan.", 
            "dur": "0.551", 
            "start": "119.899"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Right, so", 
            "dur": "0.439", 
            "start": "120.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Zheng He rose from humble beginnings\nto lose both of his testicles,", 
            "dur": "2.82", 
            "start": "120.889"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and become the greatest\nadmiral in Chinese history.", 
            "dur": "2.55", 
            "start": "123.709"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let\u2019s go to the thought Bubble.", 
            "dur": "1.271", 
            "start": "126.259"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Between 1405 and 1433,", 
            "dur": "1.339", 
            "start": "127.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Zheng He led seven voyages\nthroughout the Indian Ocean,", 
            "dur": "3.231", 
            "start": "128.869"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the expeditions of the so-called\ntreasure ships, and they were huge.", 
            "dur": "3.53", 
            "start": "132.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Columbus\u2019 first voyage\nconsisted of three ships.", 
            "dur": "2.49", 
            "start": "135.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Zheng He led an armada\nof over 300 ships.", 
            "dur": "2.61", 
            "start": "138.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "With a crew of over 27,000\u2014", 
            "dur": "1.99", 
            "start": "140.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "more than half of London\u2019s\npopulation at the time.", 
            "dur": "3.97", 
            "start": "142.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And some of these ships were,\nwell, enormous.", 
            "dur": "2.12", 
            "start": "146.69"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The flagships,\nknown as treasure ships,", 
            "dur": "2.22", 
            "start": "148.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "were over 400 feet long and\nhad 7 or more masts.", 
            "dur": "3.44", 
            "start": "151.03"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "See that little tiny ship there\nin front of the Treasure Ship?", 
            "dur": "2.93", 
            "start": "154.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That\u2019s a to-scale rendering of\nChristopher Columbus\u2019s flagship,", 
            "dur": "3.18", 
            "start": "157.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the Santa Maria.", 
            "dur": "0.95", 
            "start": "160.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Zheng He wasn\u2019t an explorer:", 
            "dur": "1.82", 
            "start": "161.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The Indian Ocean trade routes\nwere already known to him", 
            "dur": "2.22", 
            "start": "163.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and other Chinese sailors.", 
            "dur": "1.66", 
            "start": "165.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He visited Africa,\nIndia, and the Middle East,", 
            "dur": "2.34", 
            "start": "167.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and in a way,\nhis journeys were trade missions,", 
            "dur": "2.51", 
            "start": "169.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but not in the sense of filling his\nships up with stuff to", 
            "dur": "2.89", 
            "start": "172.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "be sold later for higher prices.", 
            "dur": "2.71", 
            "start": "174.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "China was the leading manufacturer\nof quality goods in the world,", 
            "dur": "2.68", 
            "start": "177.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and there wasn\u2019t anything they\nactually needed to import.", 
            "dur": "3.01", 
            "start": "180.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What they needed was prestige and respect\nso that people would continue to see China", 
            "dur": "3.97", 
            "start": "183.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as the center of the economic universe,", 
            "dur": "2.04", 
            "start": "187.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so there was a tribute system", 
            "dur": "1.3", 
            "start": "189.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "through which foreign rulers or their ambassadors\nwould come to China and engage in a debasing", 
            "dur": "4.25", 
            "start": "190.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "ritual", 
            "dur": "0.3", 
            "start": "194.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "called the kowtow", 
            "dur": "1.17", 
            "start": "195.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "wherein they acknowledged the\nsuperiority of the Chinese emperor", 
            "dur": "2.47", 
            "start": "196.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and offered him or her\nbut usually him", 
            "dur": "2.51", 
            "start": "198.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "gifts in return for the right\nto trade with China.", 
            "dur": "2.96", 
            "start": "201.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The opportunity to humble yourself\nbefore the Chinese emperor was", 
            "dur": "2.78", 
            "start": "204.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so valuable that many a prince was\nhappy to jump on a treasure ship", 
            "dur": "3.41", 
            "start": "207.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and sail back to China\nwith Zheng He.", 
            "dur": "2.35", 
            "start": "210.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Also, these tribute missions brought\nlots of crazy things to China,", 
            "dur": "3.67", 
            "start": "212.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "including exotic animals:", 
            "dur": "1.71", 
            "start": "216.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "From Africa, Zheng He brought\nback a zoo\u2019s worth of", 
            "dur": "2.62", 
            "start": "218.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "rhinos, zebras, and even giraffes.", 
            "dur": "3.12", 
            "start": "220.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Basically, he was like the\nmedieval Chinese Noah.", 
            "dur": "3.02", 
            "start": "224"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Thanks, Thought Bubble.", 
            "dur": "0.75", 
            "start": "227.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the Chinese were world\nleaders in naval technology,", 
            "dur": "2.37", 
            "start": "227.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and they wanted to dominate\ntrade here in the Indian Ocean.", 
            "dur": "2.73", 
            "start": "230.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So why, then, did these voyages end?", 
            "dur": "2.42", 
            "start": "232.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One reason was that Zheng,", 
            "dur": "0.91", 
            "start": "235.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He couldn\u2019t live forever,\nand sure enough, he didn\u2019t.", 
            "dur": "2.51", 
            "start": "236.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Also his patron,\nthe Yongle Emperor, died.", 
            "dur": "2.16", 
            "start": "238.71"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the emperor\u2019s successors weren\u2019t very\ninterested in maritime trade.", 
            "dur": "2.57", 
            "start": "240.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They were more concerned\nwith protecting China from", 
            "dur": "2.41", 
            "start": "243.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "its traditional enemies,\nnomads from the steppe.", 
            "dur": "2.93", 
            "start": "245.85"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To do this,", 
            "dur": "0.57", 
            "start": "248.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they built a Rather Famous Wall.", 
            "dur": "1.69", 
            "start": "249.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The Great Wall was mostly built under the\nMing with resources that they had because", 
            "dur": "4.36", 
            "start": "251.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they stopped building gigantic ships.", 
            "dur": "2.319", 
            "start": "255.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Just imagine what might have happened if the\nMing emperors had embraced a different strategy.", 
            "dur": "3.311", 
            "start": "257.719"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One that was based on outreach\ninstead of isolationism.", 
            "dur": "3.4", 
            "start": "261.03"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And now,\nto the blue corner\u2026", 
            "dur": "1.25", 
            "start": "264.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Representing\nPortuguese exploration,", 
            "dur": "1.449", 
            "start": "265.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we have Vasco da Gama.", 
            "dur": "1.85", 
            "start": "267.129"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Couple things about Portugal:", 
            "dur": "0.87", 
            "start": "268.979"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "First, it has a fair bit of coast line.", 
            "dur": "1.521", 
            "start": "269.849"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Secondly it was also\nrelatively resource poor,", 
            "dur": "2.139", 
            "start": "271.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which meant it relied\nupon trade to grow.", 
            "dur": "2.28", 
            "start": "273.509"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Also, the Iberian peninsula was the only place\nin Europe where Muslims could be found in", 
            "dur": "3.171", 
            "start": "275.789"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "large numbers in the 15th century,", 
            "dur": "1.549", 
            "start": "278.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which meant the Christian Crusading spirit\nwas quite strong there, presumably because", 
            "dur": "3.951", 
            "start": "280.509"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Muslims had brought so much stability\nand prosperity to the region.", 
            "dur": "3.12", 
            "start": "284.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And chief among these\nwould-be crusaders was", 
            "dur": "1.47", 
            "start": "287.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Prince Henry the Navigator,\nso called because", 
            "dur": "2.31", 
            "start": "289.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "he was not a navigator.", 
            "dur": "0.6", 
            "start": "291.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[What is in a name,\nMetta World Peace?]", 
            "dur": "0.59", 
            "start": "291.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He was, however, a patron, not only of sailors\nthemselves, but of a special school at Sagres", 
            "dur": "4.35", 
            "start": "292.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in which nautical knowledge was collected\nand new maps were made,", 
            "dur": "2.88", 
            "start": "296.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and all kinds of\nawesome stuff happened.", 
            "dur": "1.639", 
            "start": "299.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And all that knowledge gave Portuguese sailors\na huge competitive advantage when it came", 
            "dur": "3.041", 
            "start": "301.419"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to exploration.", 
            "dur": "0.87", 
            "start": "304.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Henry commissioned sailors\nto search for two things.", 
            "dur": "1.919", 
            "start": "305.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "First,", 
            "dur": "0.271", 
            "start": "307.249"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a path to the Indian Ocean\nso they could get in on", 
            "dur": "2.209", 
            "start": "307.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the lucrative spice trade.", 
            "dur": "1.481", 
            "start": "309.729"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And second,", 
            "dur": "0.44", 
            "start": "311.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to find the kingdom of Prester John,", 
            "dur": "1.729", 
            "start": "311.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a mythical Christian King who was supposed\nto live in Africa somewhere, so that Henry", 
            "dur": "3.79", 
            "start": "313.379"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "could have Prester John\u2019s help in a crusade.", 
            "dur": "2.15", 
            "start": "317.169"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Da Gama was the first\nof Henry\u2019s prot\u00e9g\u00e9s", 
            "dur": "1.69", 
            "start": "319.319"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to make it around Africa,\nand into the Indian Ocean.", 
            "dur": "3.071", 
            "start": "321.009"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In 1498,\nhe landed at Calicut,", 
            "dur": "1.57", 
            "start": "324.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a major trading center on\nIndia\u2019s west coast.", 
            "dur": "2.239", 
            "start": "325.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And when he got there, merchants\nasked him what he was looking for.", 
            "dur": "3.071", 
            "start": "327.889"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He answered with three words:", 
            "dur": "1.63", 
            "start": "330.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Gold and Christians.", 
            "dur": "1.84", 
            "start": "332.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Which basically sums up\nPortugal\u2019s reasons for exploration.", 
            "dur": "2.28", 
            "start": "334.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, once the Portuguese breached\nthe Indian Ocean,", 
            "dur": "1.979", 
            "start": "336.71"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they didn\u2019t create, like,\nhuge colonies,", 
            "dur": "1.891", 
            "start": "338.689"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because there were already\npowerful empires in the region.", 
            "dur": "2.66", 
            "start": "340.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Instead,", 
            "dur": "0.259", 
            "start": "343.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they apparently sat in the middle\nof the Indian Ocean doing nothing.", 
            "dur": "2.63", 
            "start": "343.499"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Actually, they were able to capture\n&amp; control a number of coastal cities,", 
            "dur": "3.12", 
            "start": "346.129"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "creating what historians call a", 
            "dur": "1.2", 
            "start": "349.249"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "\u201ctrading post empire.\u201d", 
            "dur": "1.37", 
            "start": "350.449"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They could do this thanks\nto their well-armed ships,", 
            "dur": "1.82", 
            "start": "351.819"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which captured cities by", 
            "dur": "0.881", 
            "start": "353.639"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "firing cannons into city walls", 
            "dur": "1.799", 
            "start": "354.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like IRL Angry Birds.", 
            "dur": "1.69", 
            "start": "356.319"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But since the Portuguese didn\u2019t\nhave enough people or boats", 
            "dur": "2.22", 
            "start": "358.009"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to run the Indian Ocean trade,", 
            "dur": "1.671", 
            "start": "360.229"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they had to rely on extortion.", 
            "dur": "0.859", 
            "start": "361.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[C.R.E.A.M. Get the money-\nDollar, dollar bill y&#39;all.]", 
            "dur": "0.731", 
            "start": "362.759"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, Portuguese merchant ships\nwould capture other ships", 
            "dur": "1.799", 
            "start": "363.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and force them to purchase\na permit to trade", 
            "dur": "2.24", 
            "start": "365.289"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "called a cartaz.", 
            "dur": "1.17", 
            "start": "367.529"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And without a cartaz,\na merchant couldn\u2019t trade", 
            "dur": "1.641", 
            "start": "368.699"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in any of the towns that\nPortugal controlled.", 
            "dur": "2.09", 
            "start": "370.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To merchants,", 
            "dur": "0.31", 
            "start": "372.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "who\u2019d plied the Indian Ocean\nfor years in relative freedom,", 
            "dur": "2.669", 
            "start": "372.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the Portuguese were\njust glorified pirates,", 
            "dur": "2.31", 
            "start": "375.409"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "extracting value from\ntrade without", 
            "dur": "1.73", 
            "start": "377.719"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "adding to its efficiency or volume.", 
            "dur": "1.881", 
            "start": "379.449"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, the cartaz strategy sort of\nworked for a while, but", 
            "dur": "2.28", 
            "start": "381.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the Portuguese never really took\ncontrol of Indian Ocean trade.", 
            "dur": "3.1", 
            "start": "383.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They were successful enough\nthat their neighbors Spain,", 
            "dur": "2.62", 
            "start": "386.71"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "became interested in their\nown route to the Indies,", 
            "dur": "2.179", 
            "start": "389.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and that brings us to Columbus.", 
            "dur": "2.12", 
            "start": "391.509"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But first, let\u2019s dispel some myths:", 
            "dur": "1.07", 
            "start": "393.629"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One:", 
            "dur": "0.34", 
            "start": "394.699"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Columbus and his crew\nknew the earth was round.", 
            "dur": "2.24", 
            "start": "395.039"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[Some folks still\naren&#39;t convinced]", 
            "dur": "0.41", 
            "start": "397.279"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He was just wrong\nabout the earth\u2019s size.", 
            "dur": "2.241", 
            "start": "397.689"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Columbus used\nPtolemy\u2019s geography", 
            "dur": "1.209", 
            "start": "399.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the Imago Mundi, based\non Muslim scholarship\u2014", 
            "dur": "2.37", 
            "start": "401.139"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and ended up overestimating\nthe size of Asia and", 
            "dur": "2.69", 
            "start": "403.509"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "underestimating the size\nof the oceans.", 
            "dur": "1.921", 
            "start": "406.199"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Two:", 
            "dur": "0.379", 
            "start": "408.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Columbus never thought\nhe\u2019d made it to China.", 
            "dur": "1.66", 
            "start": "408.499"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He called the people he\nencountered \u201cIndians\u201d because", 
            "dur": "2.1", 
            "start": "410.159"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "he thought that he\u2019d made it to", 
            "dur": "0.921", 
            "start": "412.259"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the East Indies,\nwhat we know as Indonesia.", 
            "dur": "2.56", 
            "start": "413.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Three:\nColumbus was not a lucky idiot.", 
            "dur": "2.87", 
            "start": "415.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He navigated completely unknown\nwaters primarily relying on", 
            "dur": "3.049", 
            "start": "418.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a technique known as\ndead reckoning,", 
            "dur": "1.54", 
            "start": "421.659"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in which you figure out your position\nbased on three pieces of information:", 
            "dur": "3.47", 
            "start": "423.199"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The direction you\u2019re going,", 
            "dur": "1.071", 
            "start": "426.669"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "your speed,", 
            "dur": "0.819", 
            "start": "427.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the time,", 
            "dur": "0.841", 
            "start": "428.559"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which you figure out via hourglass.", 
            "dur": "2.09", 
            "start": "429.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "With only that technology\nto guide you,", 
            "dur": "1.519", 
            "start": "431.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "its not actually that easy\nto hit a continent.", 
            "dur": "3.44", 
            "start": "433.009"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Come here people who are\nsaying he didn\u2019t hit a continent,", 
            "dur": "1.701", 
            "start": "436.449"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that he only hit some islands.", 
            "dur": "1.22", 
            "start": "438.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Come here.", 
            "dur": "0.9", 
            "start": "439.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Dahhh!", 
            "dur": "0.449", 
            "start": "440.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Oh,", 
            "dur": "0.45", 
            "start": "440.719"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it\u2019s time for the Open Letter?", 
            "dur": "3.92", 
            "start": "441.169"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "An open letter to\nthe Line of Demarcation\u2026", 
            "dur": "4.1", 
            "start": "445.089"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But first,", 
            "dur": "0.25", 
            "start": "449.189"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "let\u2019s see what\u2019s in the\nsecret compartment today.", 
            "dur": "2.051", 
            "start": "449.409"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Oh,\nits a globe. T", 
            "dur": "2.079", 
            "start": "451.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "hanks Stan!", 
            "dur": "0.701", 
            "start": "453.539"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Just what I always needed.", 
            "dur": "1.069", 
            "start": "454.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Dear Line of Demarcation,", 
            "dur": "1.14", 
            "start": "455.309"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You have so much to teach us", 
            "dur": "1.18", 
            "start": "456.449"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "about the way that the world\nused to work,", 
            "dur": "2", 
            "start": "457.629"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the way that it works now.", 
            "dur": "0.93", 
            "start": "459.629"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In 1494, Pope Alexander VI", 
            "dur": "2.771", 
            "start": "460.559"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "settled a dispute between\nPortugal and Spain by", 
            "dur": "2.559", 
            "start": "463.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "dividing the world into two parts:", 
            "dur": "2.761", 
            "start": "465.889"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The Spanish part, and\nthe Portuguese part.", 
            "dur": "2.979", 
            "start": "468.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This whole thing, at least", 
            "dur": "0.97", 
            "start": "471.629"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "according to\nPope Alexander VI,", 
            "dur": "1.63", 
            "start": "472.599"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "could be split between\nSpain and Portugal.", 
            "dur": "2.46", 
            "start": "474.229"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "At least when it came to\nso-called unclaimed land.", 
            "dur": "3.23", 
            "start": "476.689"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I mean, unclaimed by whom?", 
            "dur": "1.8", 
            "start": "479.919"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You know all the\nAmerican Indians were like,", 
            "dur": "1.431", 
            "start": "481.719"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "\u201cwait, this land is available?\nIn, in that case, we\u2019ll just,", 
            "dur": "2.449", 
            "start": "483.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we\u2019ll just keep it.", 
            "dur": "1.12", 
            "start": "485.599"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If its all the same to you.\u201d", 
            "dur": "1.461", 
            "start": "486.719"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Anyway, Line of Demarcation,", 
            "dur": "0.789", 
            "start": "488.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I have great news for you.", 
            "dur": "1.28", 
            "start": "488.969"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What Alexander VI did", 
            "dur": "1.91", 
            "start": "490.249"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "totally worked.", 
            "dur": "0.81", 
            "start": "492.159"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We haven\u2019t had a\nproblem since.", 
            "dur": "1.29", 
            "start": "492.969"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Best wishes, John Green.", 
            "dur": "1.75", 
            "start": "494.259"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, Columbus\u2019s first journey", 
            "dur": "1.15", 
            "start": "496.009"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(he made four,", 
            "dur": "0.63", 
            "start": "497.159"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the last three of which\nwere pretty calamitous)", 
            "dur": "1.65", 
            "start": "497.789"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "was tiny,", 
            "dur": "0.56", 
            "start": "499.439"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and he initially landed on a s\nmall Caribbean island he called", 
            "dur": "2.53", 
            "start": "499.999"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "San Salvador in search,\nlike the Portuguese,", 
            "dur": "2.44", 
            "start": "502.529"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of Gold and Christians.", 
            "dur": "1.03", 
            "start": "504.969"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He was able to convince", 
            "dur": "0.91", 
            "start": "505.999"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Ferdinand and Isabella\nof Spain", 
            "dur": "1.37", 
            "start": "506.909"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to fund his expedition by", 
            "dur": "1.181", 
            "start": "508.279"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "promising riches and\nconversions of the natives,", 
            "dur": "2.579", 
            "start": "509.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "hopefully to sign them up\nfor yet another crusade.", 
            "dur": "2.44", 
            "start": "512.039"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And there\u2019s a long-standing\nmyth that Columbus tricked", 
            "dur": "1.49", 
            "start": "514.479"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Ferdinand and Isabella\ninto paying for his trip,", 
            "dur": "2.021", 
            "start": "515.969"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but in fact they\u2019d commissioned\ntwo different sets of experts", 
            "dur": "2.539", 
            "start": "517.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to analyze his plans,\nboth of which agreed,", 
            "dur": "2.461", 
            "start": "520.529"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "he was [totes cray cray].", 
            "dur": "0.7", 
            "start": "522.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One called the plan,", 
            "dur": "0.92", 
            "start": "523.69"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "\u201cImpossible to any educated person.\u201d", 
            "dur": "1.77", 
            "start": "524.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But even so,", 
            "dur": "0.61", 
            "start": "526.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Ferdinand and Isabella\nfooted the bill,", 
            "dur": "1.42", 
            "start": "526.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "partly because they were\nfull of Crusading zeal", 
            "dur": "2.01", 
            "start": "528.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "after expelling the\nMuslims from Spain,", 
            "dur": "2.05", 
            "start": "530.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and partly because they were\ndesperate to get their hands", 
            "dur": "2.57", 
            "start": "532.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "on some of that pepper richness.", 
            "dur": "1.359", 
            "start": "535.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[Also some Kleenex, to help with\nthe subsequent sneezy richness?]", 
            "dur": "0.571", 
            "start": "536.399"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Columbus of course,\nfailed at finding riches\u2014", 
            "dur": "1.64", 
            "start": "536.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "he returned with\nneither spices nor gold.", 
            "dur": "1.96", 
            "start": "538.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He did create some Christians, as\nwe\u2019ll discuss in a future episode,", 
            "dur": "2.61", 
            "start": "540.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but in terms of\ngoal accomplishment,", 
            "dur": "1.829", 
            "start": "543.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Columbus was much less\nsuccessful than either", 
            "dur": "2.101", 
            "start": "545.009"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Zheng He or Vasco de Gama.", 
            "dur": "1.729", 
            "start": "547.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[and most certainly, David Yates]", 
            "dur": "0.25", 
            "start": "548.839"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But within two generations\nof Columbus,", 
            "dur": "1.56", 
            "start": "549.089"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Spain would become\nfantastically wealthy,", 
            "dur": "1.88", 
            "start": "550.649"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and for a time they were\nthe leading power in Europe.", 
            "dur": "2.3", 
            "start": "552.529"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Columbus\u2019s voyages also\nhad a huge, largely negative,", 
            "dur": "2.591", 
            "start": "554.829"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "impact on the people the Spanish\nencountered in the Americas.", 
            "dur": "2.32", 
            "start": "557.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And excitingly\nfrom my perspective,", 
            "dur": "1.88", 
            "start": "559.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "once Columbus returned\nfrom San Salvador,", 
            "dur": "1.659", 
            "start": "561.62"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we can speak for the first time\nof a truly world history.", 
            "dur": "4.62", 
            "start": "563.279"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Except for you Australia.", 
            "dur": "1.171", 
            "start": "567.899"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So who was the greatest\nmariner of the 15th century?", 
            "dur": "2.04", 
            "start": "569.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, as usual,", 
            "dur": "0.83", 
            "start": "571.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it depends on your\ndefinition of greatness.", 
            "dur": "1.649", 
            "start": "571.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[Eccleston, Tennant, Smith?\nFrak it... Adipose?]", 
            "dur": "0.401", 
            "start": "573.589"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you value", 
            "dur": "0.42", 
            "start": "573.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "administrative competence\nover ill-advised adventure,", 
            "dur": "2.33", 
            "start": "574.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "than Zheng He is\ncertainly the winner.", 
            "dur": "2.05", 
            "start": "576.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But the reason we remember\nColumbus over him", 
            "dur": "1.7", 
            "start": "578.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or Vasco de Gama", 
            "dur": "0.93", 
            "start": "580.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is that Columbus\u2019s voyages had\na lasting impact on the world,", 
            "dur": "3.229", 
            "start": "581.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "even if it wasn\u2019t\nnecessarily a positive one.", 
            "dur": "2.341", 
            "start": "584.649"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that makes me wonder what\nkind of person you\u2019d want to be:", 
            "dur": "2.06", 
            "start": "586.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A capable administrator and\nbrilliant sailor like Zheng He?", 
            "dur": "2.7", 
            "start": "589.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A daring captain like de Gama?", 
            "dur": "2.019", 
            "start": "591.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Or the bearer of a complicated\nbut famous legacy like Columbus?", 
            "dur": "3.531", 
            "start": "593.769"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let me know in comments.", 
            "dur": "1.3", 
            "start": "597.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Thanks for watching,\nand we\u2019ll see you next week.", 
            "dur": "1.679", 
            "start": "598.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Crash Course is\nproduced and directed by", 
            "dur": "1.331", 
            "start": "600.279"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Stan Muller,", 
            "dur": "0.789", 
            "start": "601.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "our script supervisor is", 
            "dur": "1.151", 
            "start": "602.399"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Danica Johnson.", 
            "dur": "0.479", 
            "start": "603.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The show is written by my", 
            "dur": "1.081", 
            "start": "604.029"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "high school history teacher", 
            "dur": "0.89", 
            "start": "605.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Raoul Meyer and myself,", 
            "dur": "1.29", 
            "start": "606"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and our graphics team is", 
            "dur": "1.38", 
            "start": "607.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Thought Bubble.", 
            "dur": "0.25", 
            "start": "608.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[Seriously, no Canadians made\nit past Stanley Cup Round 1?]", 
            "dur": "0.601", 
            "start": "608.899"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Last week\u2019s\nPhrase of the Week was,", 
            "dur": "0.69", 
            "start": "609.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "\u201cYou smell pretty.\u201d", 
            "dur": "0.98", 
            "start": "610.19"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[missed an opportunity\nfor banjo picking there...]", 
            "dur": "0.25", 
            "start": "611.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Thanks for that suggestion,\nby the way.", 
            "dur": "1.069", 
            "start": "611.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you want to suggest\nfuture phrases of the week,", 
            "dur": "1.57", 
            "start": "612.449"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you can do so in comments", 
            "dur": "1.031", 
            "start": "614.019"
